==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monoceros
<hw>Mo*noc"e*ros</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/; <grk>mo`nos</grk> alone, single + <grk>ke`ras</grk> horn.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A one-horned creature; a unicorn; a sea monster with
one horn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Mighty <qex>monoceroses</qex> with immeasured tails.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>The Unicorn, a constellation
situated to the east Orion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monochlamydeous</ent>⟦br⟧
